1
00:00:38,820 --> 00:00:40,040
=Visage and Soul=

2
00:00:40,040 --> 00:00:43,040
(The "Different Her"
Trilogy on Women's Relationships)

3
00:00:44,720 --> 00:00:47,640
=Episode 7=

4
00:00:54,160 --> 00:00:55,080
Weren't you saying on the phone

5
00:00:55,080 --> 00:00:56,800
the debt collectors broke your leg?

6
00:00:57,840 --> 00:00:59,320
What a load of crap.

7
00:01:00,000 --> 00:01:00,840
Xiaomi, Xiaomi.

8
00:01:01,680 --> 00:01:02,880
I had no other choice.

9
00:01:02,880 --> 00:01:04,480
You can't just leave me hanging, right?

10
00:01:05,040 --> 00:01:05,560
Zhiwei,

11
00:01:05,560 --> 00:01:06,680
is the money ready?

12
00:01:06,680 --> 00:01:07,760
They're all waiting.

13
00:01:08,480 --> 00:01:09,360
Mr. Luo.

14
00:01:11,880 --> 00:01:13,440
Who are you? Do I know you?

15
00:01:13,440 --> 00:01:14,360
Get out!

16
00:01:16,360 --> 00:01:17,400
Xi... Xiaomi.

17
00:01:17,400 --> 00:01:18,680
You've got to help me.

18
00:01:20,480 --> 00:01:21,600
Please, help me.

19
00:01:34,520 --> 00:01:35,640
Gotcha, didn't you?

20
00:01:36,640 --> 00:01:37,760
Fine.

21
00:01:37,760 --> 00:01:38,640
Got it.

22
00:01:40,120 --> 00:01:41,000
Xiaomi.

23
00:01:41,000 --> 00:01:41,760
What a coincidence.

24
00:01:41,760 --> 00:01:42,720
Talk to you later.

25
00:01:43,040 --> 00:01:43,960
I'm buying today.

26
00:01:43,960 --> 00:01:45,440
A bunch of our classmates are inside.

27
00:01:45,440 --> 00:01:46,600
Come join us.

28
00:01:47,320 --> 00:01:47,840
Let's go.

29
00:01:47,840 --> 00:01:49,440
They'll be thrilled to see you.

30
00:01:49,440 --> 00:01:50,400
And you're still gorgeous.

31
00:01:51,080 --> 00:01:52,880
You sure know what to say.

32
00:01:52,880 --> 00:01:53,720
Come on.

33
00:01:53,720 --> 00:01:55,440
Everyone, look who's here.

34
00:01:55,440 --> 00:01:56,480
Qiao Xiaomi!

35
00:01:56,480 --> 00:01:57,960
Xiaomi's still as pretty as ever.

36
00:01:57,960 --> 00:01:59,160
Come on, have a seat.

37
00:01:59,160 --> 00:02:00,280
She's here to celebrate

38
00:02:00,280 --> 00:02:01,880
me getting hired at Comic gallery.

39
00:02:01,880 --> 00:02:03,760
You all better drink with her.

40
00:02:03,760 --> 00:02:04,960
You got a job at the gallery?

41
00:02:05,200 --> 00:02:05,800
Yeah.

42
00:02:05,800 --> 00:02:07,040
I was going to wait until I started

43
00:02:07,040 --> 00:02:08,400
to surprise you.

44
00:02:08,400 --> 00:02:10,880
I made it through every
round of interviews.

45
00:02:11,080 --> 00:02:12,560
You'll be my boss from now on.

46
00:02:14,000 --> 00:02:16,160
You're not mad I didn't
tell you sooner, are you?

47
00:02:16,960 --> 00:02:18,200
Of course not. Congrats.

48
00:02:19,360 --> 00:02:19,960
Oh, right.

49
00:02:19,960 --> 00:02:21,760
This is our classmate, Li Xiaowen.

50
00:02:21,760 --> 00:02:22,600
Remember her?

51
00:02:22,600 --> 00:02:24,480
She used to let you copy her homework.

52
00:02:28,000 --> 00:02:28,680
Xiaomi,

53
00:02:29,000 --> 00:02:30,400
I heard you lost your memory.

54
00:02:30,400 --> 00:02:31,400
Is that true?

55
00:02:31,960 --> 00:02:33,600
I also heard Ye Xiaoduo did it.

56
00:02:33,840 --> 00:02:35,480
Ye Xiaoduo was ruthless.

57
00:02:35,640 --> 00:02:37,320
Back then, even if we all teamed up,

58
00:02:37,520 --> 00:02:38,920
we still couldn't beat her.

59
00:02:39,680 --> 00:02:40,520
Really?

60
00:02:40,520 --> 00:02:42,160
I remember she bit me once.

61
00:02:43,920 --> 00:02:46,000
This illegitimate daughter
of the Qiao family.

62
00:02:46,000 --> 00:02:47,560
She always carried around
that ragged cloth bag.

63
00:02:47,560 --> 00:02:49,400
Who knows what she kept inside.

64
00:02:49,760 --> 00:02:51,680
Maybe she stole something from Xiaomi

65
00:02:52,080 --> 00:02:53,160
and hid it in there.

66
00:02:53,240 --> 00:02:54,680
Don't touch my stuff!

67
00:02:56,120 --> 00:02:57,440
You parasite living off the Qiaos!

68
00:02:57,440 --> 00:02:58,560
Why are you acting so tough?

69
00:02:58,560 --> 00:02:59,440
Give it here!

70
00:03:04,080 --> 00:03:06,040
She was terrifying back then.

71
00:03:06,040 --> 00:03:07,360
Like a rabid dog.

72
00:03:09,080 --> 00:03:10,080
That's why

73
00:03:10,080 --> 00:03:12,360
you should stay away
from unstable people.

74
00:03:12,560 --> 00:03:14,440
Otherwise, you might not
even know what hit you.

75
00:03:15,240 --> 00:03:16,400
I'm not feeling well.

76
00:03:16,720 --> 00:03:17,360
I'm gonna head out.

77
00:03:17,600 --> 00:03:18,160
You guys have fun.

78
00:03:19,480 --> 00:03:21,000
Xiaomi.

79
00:03:21,440 --> 00:03:22,880
It's like that fire

80
00:03:22,880 --> 00:03:23,880
turned her into a
completely different person.

81
00:03:24,080 --> 00:03:25,760
She's not nearly as
spoiled as she used to be.

82
00:03:26,000 --> 00:03:26,800
Her dad just passed away.

83
00:03:26,800 --> 00:03:28,160
She's probably taking it hard.

84
00:03:28,160 --> 00:03:29,080
Probably.

85
00:03:29,080 --> 00:03:29,440
Come on.

86
00:03:29,440 --> 00:03:29,920
Come on, drink up.

87
00:03:29,920 --> 00:03:30,920
Come on.

88
00:03:39,040 --> 00:03:39,720
Are you okay,

89
00:03:39,720 --> 00:03:40,440
Miss Qiao?

90
00:03:40,440 --> 00:03:41,200
There are a lot of people here.

91
00:03:41,200 --> 00:03:42,360
You should be careful.

92
00:03:54,080 --> 00:03:55,240
How'd you get here so fast?

93
00:03:55,480 --> 00:03:57,160
I turned around after a
call, and you were gone.

94
00:03:57,760 --> 00:03:58,720
What are you doing here?

95
00:04:00,960 --> 00:04:02,000
Don't touch me.

96
00:04:08,720 --> 00:04:09,800
Thank you.

97
00:04:13,440 --> 00:04:14,240
Sorry.

98
00:04:14,840 --> 00:04:16,560
My fiancée hasn't been
feeling well lately.

99
00:04:18,280 --> 00:04:19,120
It's okay.

100
00:04:19,680 --> 00:04:20,560
You know each other?

101
00:04:21,960 --> 00:04:22,920
No, we don't.

102
00:04:24,560 --> 00:04:25,440
Really?

103
00:04:26,800 --> 00:04:27,480
Miss Qiao,

104
00:04:27,680 --> 00:04:29,000
if you're not feeling well,

105
00:04:29,880 --> 00:04:31,320
you should head home and rest.

106
00:04:32,600 --> 00:04:33,400
Then I'll get going.

107
00:04:33,400 --> 00:04:34,280
Thank you, Dr. Chen.

108
00:04:38,760 --> 00:04:39,560
(Ji Ran,)

109
00:04:40,360 --> 00:04:41,200
(how can there be someone)

110
00:04:41,200 --> 00:04:43,240
(who looks so much like you?)

111
00:04:44,200 --> 00:04:45,320
(Or...)

112
00:04:45,800 --> 00:04:47,280
(could it be that you never died?)

113
00:04:47,920 --> 00:04:49,640
(Maybe, just like Miss Qiao,)

114
00:04:50,200 --> 00:04:51,840
(you lost your memory.)

115
00:04:54,440 --> 00:04:55,240
Zhiwei,

116
00:04:55,720 --> 00:04:57,160
I tested her just now.

117
00:04:57,520 --> 00:04:58,880
She really doesn't remember.

118
00:05:04,960 --> 00:05:06,840
Who does she think she is?

119
00:05:07,320 --> 00:05:08,440
Everything she has now

120
00:05:08,440 --> 00:05:09,920
was given to her by you.

121
00:05:10,320 --> 00:05:11,120
Zhiwei,

122
00:05:11,280 --> 00:05:12,840
you're the true heir to the Qiao family.

123
00:05:14,040 --> 00:05:14,920
Listen up.

124
00:05:15,920 --> 00:05:18,160
I want her first-ever art show
to crash and burn.

125
00:05:19,520 --> 00:05:20,640
Completely.

126
00:05:21,960 --> 00:05:23,760
Pull it off, and I'll
pay whatever you want.

127
00:05:25,360 --> 00:05:26,400
Got it, Zhiwei.

128
00:05:26,400 --> 00:05:27,560
I'll do whatever you say.

129
00:05:28,720 --> 00:05:30,760
But Qin Yu's always with her.

130
00:05:31,240 --> 00:05:32,360
He's not easy to handle.

131
00:05:33,600 --> 00:05:35,240
There's no one I can't handle.

132
00:05:36,240 --> 00:05:38,040
Just do your job.

133
00:05:49,160 --> 00:05:51,120
Especially you. As her big sister,

134
00:05:51,840 --> 00:05:54,200
you loved playing with her the most

135
00:05:54,200 --> 00:05:56,200
your special game.

136
00:05:59,360 --> 00:06:00,960
Everyone knew she was jealous of you

137
00:06:00,960 --> 00:06:02,600
and wanted to take everything you had.

138
00:06:02,600 --> 00:06:05,880
I also heard that she started the fire.

139
00:06:06,360 --> 00:06:08,160
(But Dad said it was an accident.)

140
00:06:08,400 --> 00:06:09,720
(You're funny.)

141
00:06:10,200 --> 00:06:11,400
You were there.

142
00:06:12,120 --> 00:06:12,960
And you're asking me?

143
00:06:20,040 --> 00:06:21,080
Why are you still here?

144
00:06:25,080 --> 00:06:26,040
Stop trying to tough it out.

145
00:06:26,440 --> 00:06:28,360
If you catch a cold and get sick,

146
00:06:28,360 --> 00:06:29,960
who's going to honor that two-month bet?

147
00:06:34,800 --> 00:06:35,840
Was I...

148
00:06:37,400 --> 00:06:38,520
really that awful before?

149
00:06:43,240 --> 00:06:44,440
Why would you think that?

150
00:06:45,760 --> 00:06:46,760
Let me tell you something.

151
00:06:47,440 --> 00:06:49,560
You're the kindest,

152
00:06:49,800 --> 00:06:50,640
sweetest girl

153
00:06:50,960 --> 00:06:52,040
I've ever met.

154
00:06:53,080 --> 00:06:54,440
Past or present.

155
00:07:16,440 --> 00:07:18,120
What exactly happened

156
00:07:19,680 --> 00:07:21,280
between me and Ye Xiaoduo?

157
00:07:21,560 --> 00:07:23,120
Don't you remember?

158
00:07:23,880 --> 00:07:26,120
Your favorite special game.

159
00:07:27,160 --> 00:07:28,320
Do you know Ye Xiaoduo?

160
00:07:28,960 --> 00:07:30,560
She's your half-sister.

161
00:07:31,600 --> 00:07:32,440
Don't be afraid.

162
00:07:33,120 --> 00:07:34,320
Take my hand.

163
00:07:34,840 --> 00:07:36,360
I'll take you somewhere safe.

164
00:07:37,520 --> 00:07:39,360
Ye Xiaoduo had already lost her mother.

165
00:07:40,040 --> 00:07:41,120
Why did we still bully her?

166
00:07:41,120 --> 00:07:42,640
She's already dead.

167
00:07:43,120 --> 00:07:45,160
Who are you saying all this for?

168
00:07:45,720 --> 00:07:48,360
(Sometimes fate really isn't fair.)

169
00:07:48,920 --> 00:07:49,760
(Some people)

170
00:07:49,760 --> 00:07:51,120
(die in the flames.)

171
00:07:51,360 --> 00:07:52,560
(While others)

172
00:07:52,880 --> 00:07:54,720
(inherit a fortune worth billions.)

173
00:08:02,920 --> 00:08:03,960
Let go of me!

174
00:08:04,640 --> 00:08:05,800
What are you doing?

175
00:08:05,800 --> 00:08:06,680
Let go of me!

176
00:08:06,680 --> 00:08:07,480
Move.

177
00:08:17,560 --> 00:08:18,360
Xiaomi.

178
00:08:20,360 --> 00:08:21,160
Xiaomi.

179
00:08:22,880 --> 00:08:23,680
Xiaomi.

180
00:08:26,960 --> 00:08:28,520
So in that dream,

181
00:08:28,800 --> 00:08:30,560
you were the one hurting yourself.

182
00:08:34,000 --> 00:08:35,320
When I woke up this morning,

183
00:08:37,480 --> 00:08:38,840
I actually started

184
00:08:39,240 --> 00:08:40,520
to hate myself a little.

185
00:08:44,200 --> 00:08:45,440
I'll prescribe something

186
00:08:45,720 --> 00:08:47,000
to help you sleep better.

187
00:08:48,840 --> 00:08:49,520
By the way,

188
00:08:50,160 --> 00:08:51,520
how do you feel lately

189
00:08:52,280 --> 00:08:53,440
about that person?

190
00:08:56,320 --> 00:08:57,520
My feelings toward him

191
00:08:58,560 --> 00:09:00,000
are strange too.

192
00:09:02,520 --> 00:09:04,040
Sometimes he feels familiar.

193
00:09:04,040 --> 00:09:05,000
Sometimes he feels like a stranger.

194
00:09:08,200 --> 00:09:09,040
I'd suggest

195
00:09:09,320 --> 00:09:10,440
looking through old belongings.

196
00:09:11,120 --> 00:09:11,920
Or maybe

197
00:09:12,840 --> 00:09:14,920
go somewhere you two used to visit.

198
00:09:18,000 --> 00:09:18,920
Dr. Chen,

199
00:09:21,720 --> 00:09:23,560
if what I remember

200
00:09:24,720 --> 00:09:26,160
is bound to make me miserable,

201
00:09:28,480 --> 00:09:30,560
wouldn't it be better to stop now?

202
00:09:34,360 --> 00:09:35,400
Take your medicine on time.

203
00:09:35,400 --> 00:09:36,360
As for the answer,

204
00:09:36,560 --> 00:09:38,960
I think deep down,
you already want to find it.

205
00:09:46,080 --> 00:09:46,720
Hello.

206
00:09:48,120 --> 00:09:49,000
It's you.

207
00:09:55,760 --> 00:09:57,400
You look a lot like my younger brother.

208
00:09:59,160 --> 00:10:00,320
Is there anything I can help you with?

209
00:10:00,840 --> 00:10:01,480
Dr. Chen,

210
00:10:01,880 --> 00:10:03,480
has Qiao Xiaomi come to see you?

211
00:10:04,040 --> 00:10:05,080
Miss Qiao

212
00:10:06,080 --> 00:10:07,160
did come to see me.

213
00:10:07,520 --> 00:10:08,080
Why do you ask?

214
00:10:09,200 --> 00:10:10,720
Why did she come to see you?

215
00:10:12,000 --> 00:10:13,640
You're her fiancé.

216
00:10:13,640 --> 00:10:14,800
Shouldn't you

217
00:10:15,520 --> 00:10:17,240
be asking her that yourself?

218
00:10:20,640 --> 00:10:21,920
Here's the thing, Dr. Chen.

219
00:10:22,440 --> 00:10:23,680
Because of an accident,

220
00:10:23,680 --> 00:10:24,600
she lost her memory.

221
00:10:25,400 --> 00:10:26,640
But I'm not sure

222
00:10:27,000 --> 00:10:28,960
whether she'll get it back.

223
00:10:29,960 --> 00:10:31,280
I'm sorry, Mr. Qin.

224
00:10:31,760 --> 00:10:33,560
Patient confidentiality

225
00:10:33,840 --> 00:10:35,040
prevents me from saying more.

226
00:10:36,760 --> 00:10:37,560
Sorry for the trouble.

227
00:10:42,440 --> 00:10:43,280
So...

228
00:10:44,480 --> 00:10:45,960
do you really want

229
00:10:45,960 --> 00:10:47,440
Miss Qiao to regain her memory?

230
00:10:47,720 --> 00:10:49,160
Of course I do.

231
00:10:49,520 --> 00:10:51,040
She's my fiancée.

232
00:10:54,520 --> 00:10:55,360
Alright.

233
00:10:55,960 --> 00:10:57,000
I'll do my best.

234
00:10:59,680 --> 00:11:00,520
Thank you.

235
00:11:08,640 --> 00:11:10,400
(She has to remember.)

236
00:11:10,960 --> 00:11:13,160
(Otherwise, how will I know
who you really are?)

237
00:11:43,400 --> 00:11:45,480
♪We say good morning,
we say good night♪

238
00:11:45,480 --> 00:11:48,880
♪We say we miss each other,
but never speak of the hurt♪

239
00:11:50,480 --> 00:11:52,400
♪The sweeter it is,
the luckier we seem♪

240
00:11:52,400 --> 00:11:56,360
♪Yet the more romantic,
the rougher the road♪

241
00:11:57,600 --> 00:11:59,480
♪Let me go, set me free♪

242
00:11:59,480 --> 00:12:03,520
♪Let me drown in reckless silence♪

243
00:12:04,040 --> 00:12:09,480
♪We were perfect for each other,
yet you never admitted it♪

244
00:12:10,800 --> 00:12:12,960
♪The freedom you gave me♪

245
00:12:12,960 --> 00:12:16,600
♪Became the heaviest chain I bear♪

246
00:12:17,840 --> 00:12:20,120
♪Love can barely move forward♪

247
00:12:20,120 --> 00:12:23,920
♪Yet the words still linger unspoken♪

248
00:12:25,000 --> 00:12:27,240
♪The closeness I long for♪

249
00:12:27,240 --> 00:12:31,640
♪There's no need for you
to keep avoiding it♪

250
00:12:32,040 --> 00:12:33,880
♪I don't want to break free♪

251
00:12:33,880 --> 00:12:39,240
♪Take back the chains
disguised as freedom♪

